Bits of material found on other pages, particularly pages during heated discussion, that may be worthwhile.

 On banning 
Banning someone seems to me to be a serious matter, and not something which we should just decide by a simple poll. Polltaking leads to a dynamic where people start thinking about Do I want him banned? rather than something like Would it be right to ban him?, and also a dynamic where people feel compelled to defend their prior opinions rather than taking in facts and arguments. Some thought and discussion, hopefully leading to something close to consensus, would be good. Also, it seems there are more possibilities here than a simple binary decision. Im even leery of the discussion happening without facetoface contact among all interested, though it is possible to do it online well if everyone puts some care into it. A second concern is that some people may have thoughts they want to share without identifying themselves to everyone. Users/AlexanderWoo (at 1PMish, Sunday Oct. 30)

