Satirical and Parody Pages

I think it is important that satirical or parody pages have a readlily apparent notice that they are, in fact a work of satire or parody and are not factual.  The Jewish Slate page is a case in point.  Whereas the majority of wiki readers would recognise the parody/satire (Im still not quite sure which one it is), many of our readers may not be well versed in other cultures and subtle humor.  Imagine a freshman student at UCD fresh from the midwest.  The student might very well know nothing of Jewish values and humor.  The page could be terribly misinterpreted.  If we allow unrestrained satire and parody, whats to stop wiki pages like http://landoverbaptist.org?

I think that the Daviswiki should firstly be a source of accurate information.  I love parody and satire as much as or more than most, but when we present information that can be construed as fact but in reality is something completely different, we have strayed from the mission. Users/GrumpyoldGeek
